results.deck: Founded by Jordan Weisman and L. Ross Babcock III, FASA has created successful new game worlds since 1980.
results.description:
Overview

FASA Interactive was acquired by Microsoft in 1999. The company developed games exclusive to Microsoft platforms, both Windows PC and Xbox. Its headquarters were located in Redmond, WA, only a few miles from Microsoft's main campus. The studio was officially shutdown on September 12, 2007; more than half the studio's employees were provided with positions within Microsoft Game Studios.

On October 15, 2007, Smith & Tinker announced it had acquired licenses from Microsoft the rights for Weisman's previous works such as Shadow Run, MechWarrior, Crimson Skies and other FASA creations. Nothing is known what Smith & Tinker is doing with the aforementioned works.
